descp2: 1D integer tensor representing the shape of the binary dropout mask that will be multiplied with the input. For instance, if your inputs have shape`(batch_size, timesteps, features)` and you want the dropout mask to be the same for all timesteps, you can use `noise_shape=(batch_size, 1, features)`.
